01:55.480 --> 01:59.080
Hey, Curt, you guys gonna have
a little bash your last night in town?

01:59.160 --> 02:00.560
Moose has been
lookin' for you all day.

02:00.640 --> 02:03.400
He got worried. Thought you were
tryin' to avoid him.

02:03.480 --> 02:06.120
What do you got?

02:06.200 --> 02:10.600
- Oh, great.
- That's $2,000, man. $2,000!

02:10.680 --> 02:14.000
Mr.Jennings gave it to me
to give to you. He's sorry it's late.

02:14.040 --> 02:16.400
It's the first scholarship
the Moose Lodge has given out.

02:16.520 --> 02:19.800
He says they're all very proud of you
back at the lodge.

02:19.880 --> 02:23.040
- Why don't you hold it for me?
- I don't want it. Take it. It's yours.

02:23.120 --> 02:24.320
I'll take it.

02:26.720 --> 02:29.360
Listen, your sister calls.
I'll talk to you later.

02:29.440 --> 02:32.000
- Wait a second. She can wait.
- Make it short and sweet, huh?

02:32.080 --> 02:36.240
Listen, I don't think
I'm gonna be going tomorrow.

02:37.880 --> 02:40.080
Come on.
What are you talking about?

02:40.200 --> 02:44.840
I was thinkin' I could wait a year,
go to City for a while.

02:44.920 --> 02:46.800
You chicken fink.

02:46.880 --> 02:48.760
After all we went through
to get accepted?

02:49.520 --> 02:51.400
We're gettin' out of
this turkey town...

02:51.440 --> 02:55.120
and now you wanna crawl
back into your cell?

02:57.600 --> 03:00.520
You wanna end up like John?
You just can't stay 17 forever.

03:00.600 --> 03:04.400
- Get that through your head!
- I just need some time.

03:04.440 --> 03:07.520
I gotta go talk to Laurie.
Now take it. Take it!

03:07.600 --> 03:09.720
We're leaving in the morning,
all right?

03:10.720 --> 03:13.200
We're leaving
in the morning!

03:20.680 --> 03:24.400
We gonna rock and roll ourselves
to death, baby!

03:24.440 --> 03:26.800
You got the Wolfman Jack Show!

04:01.800 --> 04:04.200
Don't with the thing!

04:04.240 --> 04:06.680
Will you stop it
with the Big Bopper stuff?

04:06.760 --> 04:08.880
- Hi,John!
- Not too good, huh?

04:08.920 --> 04:12.600
Why is it every girl around here
is ugly or has a boyfriend?

04:12.680 --> 04:16.680
Where is the dazzling beauty
I've been searching for all my life?

04:16.720 --> 04:20.880
I know what you mean.
The pickings are really gettin' slim.

04:20.959 --> 04:22.880
The whole strip is shrinkin'.

04:24.920 --> 04:27.120
You know, I remember
about five years ago...

04:27.200 --> 04:29.960
it would take a couple of hours
and a tank full of gas...

04:30.000 --> 04:32.240
just to make one circuit.

04:32.760 --> 04:34.600
It was really somethin'.

04:40.400 --> 04:43.480
Hey,John.
Someone new in town.

04:44.920 --> 04:46.200
Are you gonna go after him?

04:46.280 --> 04:48.680
Hey, listen, professor.

04:48.720 --> 04:51.960
If he can't find me, then he ain't
even worth racin', right?

04:52.040 --> 04:54.200
Big shot.

04:54.280 --> 04:56.320
Well?

04:58.320 --> 04:59.800
Where was I?

05:00.680 --> 05:02.760
How you thought
high school romances were goofy...

05:02.800 --> 05:05.560
and we started dating only because
you thought I was cute and funny...

05:05.640 --> 05:07.640
but then you suddenly realized...

05:07.720 --> 05:09.520
you were in love with me,
it was serious

05:13.560 --> 05:16.280
You were leadin' up
to somethin' kinda big.

05:16.360 --> 05:18.520
You make it sound like
I'm giving dictation.

05:21.360 --> 05:23.640
Well, seriously...

05:23.720 --> 05:25.760
what I meant was that...

05:25.960 --> 05:28.520
since we do care for each other
so much...

05:28.600 --> 05:33.760
and since we should really consider
ourselves as adults now

05:37.000 --> 05:39.200
Could I have a couple
of those fries?

05:41.600 --> 05:43.440
Where was I?

05:43.520 --> 05:45.360
- Consider ourselves adults.
- Right, right.

05:45.440 --> 05:49.480
I thought,
maybe before I leave...

05:49.520 --> 05:51.520
we could agree that...

05:54.560 --> 05:58.520
seeing other people while I'm away
can't possibly hurt, you know?

06:05.160 --> 06:08.880
- You mean dating other people?
- It would strengthen our relationship.

06:08.960 --> 06:12.040
Then we'd know for sure
that we're really in love.

06:12.080 --> 06:14.040
Not that there's any doubt.

06:22.920 --> 06:24.840
I think you're right.

06:24.920 --> 06:27.920
I mean, we're not kids anymore...

06:27.960 --> 06:30.480
and it's silly to think
that when we're 3,000 miles apart...

06:30.520 --> 06:33.000
we shouldn't be able
to see other people and go out.

06:33.040 --> 06:35.240
Laurie, listen.
I didn't ask for that back.

06:35.280 --> 06:38.200
I know. I just sort of think
it's juvenile now.

06:38.280 --> 06:40.240
I'll keep it at home.
It's less conspicuous there.

06:40.320 --> 06:42.360
- You don't wanna wear it?
- I didn't say that.

06:42.440 --> 06:45.000
I understand,
and I'm not upset.

06:45.040 --> 06:49.320
I can't expect you to be a monk
while you're away.

06:50.360 --> 06:52.280
I got a really neat
record collection.

06:52.360 --> 06:54.960
I even got "Pledging My Love"
by Johnny Ace.

06:55.000 --> 06:57.520
How can you love Nelson when
he's going out with Marilyn Gator?

06:57.560 --> 07:00.520
- Since he dumped on you--
- He didn't dump on me, you little dip!

07:00.560 --> 07:02.720
Oh, hi, Steve.

07:03.400 --> 07:04.800
Hey, sis.

07:10.000 --> 07:12.600
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

07:12.680 --> 07:14.680
- What is it?
- Nothing!

07:16.400 --> 07:20.600
I've decided to let you take care
of my car while I'm away.

07:20.680 --> 07:22.200
At least until Christmas.

07:22.280 --> 07:24.120
I'm comin' back for a couple
of weeks at Christmas.

07:24.200 --> 07:28.400
I've got some very simple instructions
for you. Here's the keys.

07:28.480 --> 07:31.960
First of all,
only 30-weight Castrol-R.

07:32.040 --> 07:35.400
I've written the tire pressure
and stuff on a pad in the glove

07:35.440 --> 07:37.720
- Are you listening?
- Hey, what's wrong?

07:38.520 --> 07:42.160
- Are you crying?
- I can't believe it!

07:43.080 --> 07:45.080
I don't know what to say!

07:45.160 --> 07:48.760
I'll love and protect this car
until death do us part.

07:48.840 --> 07:50.920
This is a super fine machine.

07:50.960 --> 07:53.840
This might even be better than
Darryl Starbird's superfeck moon

07:53.920 --> 07:57.720
It is! It's better than
Darryl Starbird's superfeck moonbird.

07:57.800 --> 07:59.240
Budda?

08:00.760 --> 08:03.520
How'd you like to go
to the drive-in movies with me?

08:03.600 --> 08:07.280
- You gotta be kidding.
- Would I kid about a thing like that?

08:07.360 --> 08:09.200
I have a new car.

08:14.440 --> 08:16.280
Did she do that to you?

08:16.360 --> 08:19.160
Curt, you wanna bomb around?
I wanna try out my new wheels.

08:19.240 --> 08:21.080
Well, I'd like to, Toad...

08:21.160 --> 08:23.280
but I'm gonna go
with Steve and Laurie to the hop.

08:23.320 --> 08:27.160
- Besides, I'd spoil your luck.
- Yeah, right.

08:27.240 --> 08:29.320
Tonight, things are gonna be
different.

08:29.360 --> 08:33.240
Wait a minute.
You're goin' to the freshman hop?

08:33.320 --> 08:35.520
Come on, man!
That place is for kids.

08:35.600 --> 08:38.360
You two just got your ass outta there.
Don't go back there.

08:38.440 --> 08:39.919
You ain't got no emotions?

08:40.000 --> 08:43.799
We are going to remember
all of the good times.

08:43.880 --> 08:46.680
- Yeah, well, go.
- Why don'tyou come with us?

08:46.760 --> 08:49.840
- Bullshit, man!
- Come on. For old times' sake.

08:49.920 --> 08:52.240
Listen, you go.
Go ahead, Curtsie baby.

08:52.320 --> 08:55.240
You go on over there and remember
the good times you won't be havin'.

08:55.280 --> 08:57.560
I ain't goin' off to some
god damn fancy college.

08:57.640 --> 09:01.160
I'm stayin' right here--
havin' fun as usual!

09:02.800 --> 09:06.320
Jesus, Milner, you're really
in a great mood tonight!

09:06.400 --> 09:08.680
What's the matter,John?

09:12.040 --> 09:14.360
Did I do somethin' wrong?
I'm sorry.

09:14.440 --> 09:16.520
Man, it's nothin'.

09:18.840 --> 09:21.680
- We'll see you later, okay?
- All right.

09:21.760 --> 09:24.840
We'll all do somethin' together
before Steve leaves.

09:26.120 --> 09:29.520
Wait a minute.
Now you're not goin'?

09:29.560 --> 09:31.360
I don't know.

10:13.360 --> 10:16.600
- Hey, Milner!
- What happened to your fat head?

10:17.600 --> 10:19.960
- What happened to your fat head?
- Your mother!

10:21.720 --> 10:24.920
Your mother!
Hey, we been talkin' 'bout you.

10:25.920 --> 10:29.040
There's a very wicked
'55 Chevy lookin' for you.

10:29.120 --> 10:33.120
- Yeah, I know.
- Watch out for the cop at Jerry's.

10:33.240 --> 10:34.560
Yeah, all right. Thanks.

10:50.640 --> 10:52.160
Hey, Toad!

10:52.240 --> 10:54.960
Is that you
in that beautiful car?

10:55.040 --> 10:58.000
Jeez, what a waste
of machinery!

11:10.160 --> 11:11.760
Hey, kid!

11:24.000 --> 11:27.480
All right, baby.
Here we go with another call.

11:28.560 --> 11:32.680
-Answer the phone, dummy.
- Pinkie's Pizza.

11:32.720 --> 11:35.600
You got anymore of those
secret agent spy scoops?

11:35.720 --> 11:37.080
Hit parade
on astethoscope?

11:37.160 --> 11:39.960
No, secret agent spyscope, man...

11:40.040 --> 11:41.920
that pulls in the moon,
stars, the planets...

11:42.000 --> 11:44.920
and the satellites
and little bitty spacemen.

11:45.040 --> 11:46.880
You have the wrong number,
partner.

12:01.360 --> 12:03.200
Wait!
What did you say?

12:04.720 --> 12:06.560
Quick. Quick.
Hang a right.

12:06.640 --> 12:09.120
- What? Why?
- Steven, cut over to "G" Street.

12:09.200 --> 12:12.480
I just saw a vision.
I saw a goddess.

12:12.560 --> 12:13.920
Come on.
You gotta catch up to her.

12:14.000 --> 12:15.880
- I didn't see anything.
- Come on, Curt.

12:15.920 --> 12:18.800
We can't be spendin' half the night
chasing girls down for you.

12:18.880 --> 12:24.080
Laurie, this was the most perfect,
dazzling creature I've ever seen!

12:24.160 --> 12:26.480
- She's gone. Forget it.
- She spoke to me.

12:26.560 --> 12:30.320
She spoke to me through the window!
I think she said, "I love you".

12:31.760 --> 12:33.720
That means nothing
to you people?

12:33.840 --> 12:37.360
You have no romance,
no soul?

12:37.440 --> 12:41.480
Someone wants me. Someone
roaming the streets wants me.

12:41.520 --> 12:43.440
Will you turn the corner?

12:48.720 --> 12:50.720
- Later.
- Alligator.

13:03.080 --> 13:04.840
You're new around here.
Where you from?

13:04.880 --> 13:08.280
- Turlock.
- You know a guy named Frank Bartlett?

13:08.400 --> 13:10.560
No. Does he go to Turlock High?

13:10.640 --> 13:13.080
Well, he used to.
He goes to J.C. now.

13:13.200 --> 13:16.320
- Do you go to J.C.?
- Yeah, sure.

13:16.400 --> 13:18.800
Wow! Do you know Guy Phillips?

13:18.920 --> 13:21.080
Yeah, sure.
I got him in a class.

13:21.160 --> 13:22.880
He's so boss!

13:22.960 --> 13:25.640
How'd you like to ride around
with me for a while?

13:25.680 --> 13:27.920
I'm sorry. I can't.
I'm going steady.

13:29.640 --> 13:33.200
- Come on!
- I just can't.

13:33.280 --> 13:35.080
You're just ridin' around
with a bunch of girls.

13:35.120 --> 13:38.000
Anybody else in there
wanna go for a ride?

13:40.080 --> 13:42.840
You got nothin' to fear.
I'm as harmless as a baby kitten.

13:42.920 --> 13:47.040
- I'll go! I'll go!
-Judy's sister'll go with you, okay?

13:47.120 --> 13:50.560
Yeah, sure.
Judy, her sister, her mother...

13:50.640 --> 13:52.520
Anybody.
I'll take 'em all.

13:52.560 --> 13:55.000
Listen. We'll go up
and stop at that light.

13:55.120 --> 13:58.400
It'll turn red by the time we get there.
All right?

13:58.480 --> 14:01.760
If you ever get tired of going steady
with somebody that ain't around...

14:01.840 --> 14:04.080
I'm up for grabs.

14:25.440 --> 14:29.000
So, you're Judy's little--
Shit! How old are you?

14:29.520 --> 14:31.240
I'm old enough.
How old are you?

14:31.280 --> 14:33.760
- I'm too old for you.
- You can't be that old.

14:33.840 --> 14:36.720
I think you better go back
and sit with your sister.

14:36.840 --> 14:40.400
Where are they anyway? Are they
comin' back? This is a joke, right?

14:40.480 --> 14:43.000
This better be a joke,
'cause I'm not drivin' you around!

14:43.120 --> 14:46.400
You asked me. What's the matter?
Am I too ugly?

14:47.440 --> 14:51.200
Judy doesn't want me with her,
and now you don't want me with you.

14:51.280 --> 14:55.160
Nobody wants me.
Even my mother and father hate me.

14:55.280 --> 14:58.120
- Everybody hates me.
- They don't hate ya.

14:58.160 --> 15:01.800
- You throw me out, I'll scream.
- No, no. Stay cool.

15:01.840 --> 15:04.720
Everything's all right.
We'll find your sister.

15:04.840 --> 15:08.560
- Can't be too hard to find.
-John, you gonna be there tonight?

15:08.640 --> 15:10.200
Shit! Hey, get down.

15:15.440 --> 15:20.480
- Is this called "copping a feel"?
- What? No! Get up. Jesus.

15:20.560 --> 15:23.000
- What's your name?
- My name?

15:23.120 --> 15:25.280
Mud, if anybody sees you.

15:35.040 --> 15:38.640
- What do you got in there, kid?
- More than you can handle.

16:05.440 --> 16:07.400
Excuse me.
I think we've had an accident.

16:07.520 --> 16:11.200
Damn it, I won't report you this time,
but next time,just watch it!

16:32.560 --> 16:35.760
- Good evening. How are ya?
- Yeah, hi.

16:35.840 --> 16:39.520
This is really a beautiful car,
you know? Of course you know it.

16:39.600 --> 16:41.600
You know what I'd like to give you
for this car?

16:41.680 --> 16:44.000
I'd like to give you $1,000!

16:44.080 --> 16:47.120
I can't give you that, but I'm not gonna
give you a whole line.

16:47.200 --> 16:50.160
I'm gonna tell you
what I can give you. Come over here.

16:50.240 --> 16:54.000
How would you like, for $525,
to own this practically new 'Vette?

16:54.080 --> 16:55.920
I'll tell you what
I'm going to do.

16:56.000 --> 16:59.440
I'm gonna knock ten percent
right off the top. How about that?

16:59.560 --> 17:02.720
- That's $98 down.
- No, I'm sorry.

17:02.800 --> 17:05.599
$98 a month.
You ask me how can I do this?

17:05.680 --> 17:08.040
I'll tell you
how I can do it.

17:08.079 --> 17:10.800
My boss wants to get rid
of the sporty cars.

17:10.880 --> 17:13.760
- You all right?
- I'm fine.

17:13.839 --> 17:15.359
I don't think it's a good idea.

17:15.440 --> 17:17.800
- I'm busy.
- I want you to listen.

17:17.839 --> 17:20.400
I've gotta go!

17:20.480 --> 17:22.760
Leave me alone,
for God's sake!

17:25.960 --> 17:28.240
One, two, three, four

17:41.360 --> 17:43.080
At the hop

17:46.240 --> 17:49.360
You can rock it, you can roll it
Do the stomp, even stroll it at the hop

17:50.440 --> 17:53.680
When there cords start spinnin,you
can mix it with the chicken at the hop

17:54.800 --> 17:57.640
Do the dance sensation
that's sweepin' the nation at the hop

17:59.680 --> 18:03.120
Let's go to the hop

18:13.280 --> 18:15.760
You can swing, you can groove it, you
can really start to move it at the hop

18:17.360 --> 18:21.200
Where the jockey is the smoothest
And the music is the coolest at the hop

18:21.680 --> 18:24.560
All the guys and chicks
can get their kicks at the hop

18:38.800 --> 18:39.680
Let's go!

19:03.360 --> 19:05.720
Why are you so depressed?

19:05.800 --> 19:08.000
You'll forget him in a week.

19:08.080 --> 19:11.800
After you're elected Senior Queen,
you'll have so many boys after your bod.

19:11.880 --> 19:15.920
Peggy, the point is, I do not want
to go out with any other guys.

19:16.000 --> 19:20.320
Laurie, I know
it's a drag, but you can't just--

19:20.400 --> 19:23.360
Remember what happened
to Evelyn Chelnick?

19:23.440 --> 19:26.560
When Mike went into the Marines,
she had a nervous breakdown...

19:26.640 --> 19:29.520
and was acting so wacky
she got run over by a bus.

19:31.280 --> 19:33.160
I just wish I could
go with him.

19:33.200 --> 19:35.720
Laurie,jeez! Come on.

19:38.640 --> 19:40.480
Hey, zit makeup!
Hey, everybody--

19:40.560 --> 19:42.800
Just cool it, Steve?

19:45.840 --> 19:47.920
Let me see
some of that stuff.

19:48.000 --> 19:49.360
You leavin' tomorrow?

19:50.400 --> 19:53.640
- You and Laurie engaged yet?
- No, but we got it all worked out.

19:53.680 --> 19:56.120
We're still gonna be goin' together,
but we can date other people.

19:56.200 --> 19:58.480
And screw around.
I know.

19:58.560 --> 20:00.800
Hey, I hear college girls
really put out.

20:07.800 --> 20:10.120
When I saw her
standing there

20:10.160 --> 20:13.040
I had to pick her up
I couldn't fail

20:13.120 --> 20:18.760
'Cause I knew
I had to make her mine

20:18.800 --> 20:21.920
She's so cool
She's so fine

20:26.440 --> 20:29.320
I was tryin' to think
of words to say

20:29.360 --> 20:32.560
So I went up to her
and changed my fate

20:35.760 --> 20:38.120
- Come on.
- "Come on" what?

20:39.120 --> 20:41.480
- Let's dance.
- No, thanks.

20:43.440 --> 20:47.640
- Laurie, I said I wanna dance.
- Who's stopping you?

20:47.720 --> 20:51.880
I thought you might wanna dance with me
our last night together.

20:51.920 --> 20:54.480
How sentimental of you.
You'll be back at Christmas.

20:54.560 --> 20:57.680
- I want to dance now, not at Christmas.
- Get your cooties off me!

21:06.760 --> 21:09.480
- Don't make a scene.
- Go ahead. Slug me. Scar my face!

21:09.520 --> 21:12.400
I wouldn't dance with you
if you were the last guy in this gym.

21:12.480 --> 21:15.360
- This is getting good.
- Come on, Eddie, I'll dance with you.

21:15.440 --> 21:17.440
You don't mind, do you, Peggy?

21:19.920 --> 21:21.800
Joe College strikes out.

22:13.320 --> 22:15.760
Feel so good

22:16.240 --> 22:18.720
Take me by my hand

22:32.000 --> 22:35.440
And let's go strollin'

22:35.520 --> 22:38.320
In Wonderland

22:45.200 --> 22:47.680
Curtis, come here.
Help me, will ya? I'm surrounded.

22:47.760 --> 22:50.640
- Come here.
- You won't dance? Come on.

22:50.720 --> 22:52.560
No, really, I'd like to,
but I can't.

22:52.640 --> 22:55.680
I fold Mr. Simpson saw me dancing
with one of you sexy little--

22:55.760 --> 22:59.200
excuse me --one ofyou young ladies,
he'd have my rear end.

23:03.440 --> 23:06.400
Come on, gentlemen, back inside.
Put it out. Let's go.

23:06.480 --> 23:09.640
Kids! Want a cigarette?

23:10.720 --> 23:12.560
All right.

23:13.760 --> 23:16.840
- I thought you'd left.
- No, not yet. I have no matches.

23:16.880 --> 23:19.520
That's all right.

23:20.800 --> 23:25.560
Brother! How do I get stuck
with dance supervision?

23:25.640 --> 23:27.760
You goin' back east?

23:27.840 --> 23:32.320
I remember the day I went off.
Got drunk as hell the night before.

23:32.400 --> 23:35.080
- Blotto.
- Blotto. Exactly.

23:35.120 --> 23:39.200
- Barfed on the train all the next day.
- Cute. Very cute.

23:40.080 --> 23:41.200
Where'd you go again?

23:41.360 --> 23:43.280
Middlebury. Vermont.

23:43.360 --> 23:46.000
- Got a scholarship.
- Only stayed a semester.

23:46.080 --> 23:48.480
One semester, after all that.
Came back here.

23:48.560 --> 23:50.440
Why'd you come back?

23:50.480 --> 23:53.640
Decided I wasn't
the competitive type.

23:53.680 --> 23:55.560
I don't know.
Maybe I was scared.

23:57.760 --> 24:00.880
Well, I think I may find
that I'm not...

24:00.960 --> 24:03.160
the competitive type myself.

24:03.240 --> 24:08.440
- What do you mean?
- I'm not really sure that I'm going.

24:08.520 --> 24:11.600
