Oh, brother!

32:53.280 --> 32:55.880
Even after that, you didn't call me
for two weeks.

32:55.960 --> 33:00.240
- I was busy.
- You were scared. Dave Ogler told me.

33:00.280 --> 33:03.520
When you did ask me out,
you didn't kiss me for three dates.

33:03.600 --> 33:06.960
- Well, I was--
- Scared. Jim Kiler told me.

33:08.000 --> 33:10.120
I even asked my father
why you hadn't kissed me.

33:10.200 --> 33:13.160
- Your father. Great.
- You know what he said?

33:13.240 --> 33:15.240
He said he thought
you were bright enough...

33:15.320 --> 33:18.640
and that you'd probably
get around to it after a while.

33:18.720 --> 33:21.080
You didn't, of course.
I had to.

33:22.480 --> 33:25.160
Remember the picnic?

33:25.240 --> 33:26.960
Out at the canyon?

33:27.120 --> 33:30.000
Boy! You don't remember
anything, do you?

33:30.160 --> 33:32.880
The first one,
up at the lake.

33:32.920 --> 33:35.000
That was the first time
you kissed me.

33:36.880 --> 33:40.560
I had to practically
throw myself at you.

33:40.640 --> 33:41.800
I remember.

34:08.960 --> 34:10.440
What's wrong?

34:10.520 --> 34:12.080
Go to hell.

34:18.560 --> 34:21.199
What are you doin',
stealin' hubcaps?

34:21.280 --> 34:24.719
- Well, hey, Wendy.
- How've you been?

34:24.840 --> 34:26.800
Fine.

34:26.880 --> 34:30.920
- Great. How you been?
- Wait a sec.

34:31.000 --> 34:32.880
Wait a minute!

34:33.600 --> 34:35.520
Bobbie Tucker.
She's got her car.

34:37.280 --> 34:40.480
- Heard you're going away to school.
- Maybe, maybe.

34:42.400 --> 34:44.159
- What?
- Same old Curt.

34:44.239 --> 34:48.159
All the time we were going together,
you never knew what you were doing.

34:51.120 --> 34:55.040
- I gotta go.
- Where ya goin'?

34:55.159 --> 34:58.000
- Nowhere.
- You mind if I come along?

34:58.040 --> 35:00.640
- Okay.
- Okay.

35:02.600 --> 35:04.640
Louie, Louie

35:06.160 --> 35:08.000
Me gotta go

35:09.640 --> 35:13.280
A fine little girl
She's waitin' for me

35:13.360 --> 35:17.040
Catch a ship
across the sea

35:17.120 --> 35:20.960
Sail the ship all alone

35:21.040 --> 35:24.400
Never think
I'll make it home

35:41.320 --> 35:44.720
All right, Bolander, break that up.
You know the rules.

35:44.800 --> 35:48.080
You and your girlfriend wanna do that,
go someplace else, huh?

35:48.160 --> 35:51.120
Hey, Kroot.
Why don't you go kiss a duck?

35:51.240 --> 35:54.640
- What did you say?
- I said go kiss a duck, marble-head.

35:54.720 --> 35:58.000
All right, Bolander,
you are suspended.

35:58.040 --> 36:01.080
Don't you even come in Monday.
You're out!

36:03.120 --> 36:05.240
I graduated last semester.
Remember?

36:23.520 --> 36:26.160
Why don't we go out
to the canal?

36:26.240 --> 36:28.560
What for?

36:28.600 --> 36:30.920
Listen, I can get tough
with you too, you know.

36:30.960 --> 36:33.040
Hard guy.

36:50.080 --> 36:54.160
A double Chubby Chuck, a chili-barb,
two orders of French fries and--

36:54.240 --> 36:56.760
- Cherry Coke.
- And two Cherry Cokes.

36:58.240 --> 37:00.120
What?

37:01.200 --> 37:02.480
Right. Cool.

37:04.080 --> 37:06.600
Hey, Deb.
How's my soft baby?

37:06.680 --> 37:08.520
Come on. Beat it, Vic.
I'm not your baby.

37:09.560 --> 37:12.880
Come on, honey.
So I never called you back.

37:12.960 --> 37:14.840
I been, you know, busy.

37:14.920 --> 37:16.720
Yeah, three weeks?

37:16.800 --> 37:18.800
Besides, it only took me one night
to realize...

37:18.880 --> 37:21.280
if brains were dynamite,
you couldn't blow your nose.

37:21.360 --> 37:25.360
Look who's talking. Who's the wimp
you're hangin' out with now? Einstein?

37:25.440 --> 37:28.400
Tiger happens to be
very intelligent, unlike you.

37:28.520 --> 37:32.960
I know everything your dirty little mind
is thinking. It shows.

37:33.040 --> 37:35.880
Hey, now, buddy, look.
The lady obviously doesn't want--

37:35.920 --> 37:38.000
Look, creep. You want
a knuckle sandwich?

37:38.120 --> 37:40.920
No, thanks. I'm waitin'
for a double Chubby Chuck.

37:41.000 --> 37:42.560
Then keep your smart-ass
mouth shut.

37:42.640 --> 37:44.400
I'll call you sometime, Deb.

37:44.520 --> 37:48.000
- Some night when I'm hard up.
- I won't be home.

37:50.120 --> 37:52.160
Get out of here.

37:53.560 --> 37:55.560
You seem to know
a lot of weird guys.

37:55.640 --> 37:59.200
That creep's not a friend of mine.
He's just horny.

37:59.280 --> 38:02.160
That's why I like you.
You're different.

38:02.200 --> 38:05.360
I-- I am? I mean,
you really think I'm intelligent?

38:05.440 --> 38:08.960
Yeah. And I bet you're smart enough
to get us some brew.

38:12.080 --> 38:15.160
Brew? Oh, liquor.

38:19.160 --> 38:21.280
Yeah, this place is
too crowded anyway.

38:31.800 --> 38:36.520
What about your hamburgers
and Cokes, sir?

38:39.240 --> 38:42.320
Will you speed up?
You're gonna lose her.

38:42.440 --> 38:46.160
Cut around him.
Just hang a right at the corner.

38:46.200 --> 38:48.560
Lost her again.

38:48.680 --> 38:51.280
- Who is she?
- I don't know.

38:51.400 --> 38:53.160
But I'm gonna find out.

38:54.400 --> 38:56.160
I know who she is.

39:00.240 --> 39:02.000
Well, come on, Bob.

39:03.360 --> 39:05.240
Come on! Who is she?

39:06.480 --> 39:08.280
Come on!

39:08.400 --> 39:12.040
You know Mr. Beeman?
He owns Hepcat Jewelers?

39:14.000 --> 39:15.800
That's his wife.

39:15.920 --> 39:17.880
Get outta here.

39:18.000 --> 39:20.680
That's ridiculous.
That girl is young and beautiful.

39:20.760 --> 39:23.640
- And married.
- And she was cruising Tenth Street.

39:23.760 --> 39:26.200
You gotta be thinkin'
of someone else.

39:26.320 --> 39:30.480
Did you know that my ex is going
to become a presidential aide?

39:33.920 --> 39:37.200
It's a secret, so don't tell anybody,
but his greatest ambition...

39:37.280 --> 39:39.600
is to shake hands
with President Kennedy.

39:41.280 --> 39:44.880
How do you suppose you're gonna
do that, wishy-washy, at J.C.?

39:45.000 --> 39:47.600
Maybe I've grown up.
Maybe I changed my mind.

39:47.720 --> 39:50.520
- Doubt it.
- Maybe you don't think you can do it.

39:50.640 --> 39:53.200
- Maybe you oughta shut up.
- Maybe I ought to, but I won't.

39:53.320 --> 39:56.200
Maybe you oughta
come into the aft chamber...

39:56.280 --> 39:58.600
where we can
discuss this in private.

40:03.120 --> 40:05.200
Thanks a lot.

40:05.720 --> 40:07.320
Come on, Wendy.

40:13.360 --> 40:16.240
Move over.
I'm not sitting on your lap.

40:19.440 --> 40:22.360
- To the opera, James.
- Drop dead.

40:22.480 --> 40:24.600
Unless you want to go to Gallo Dam
and have a little orgy.

40:24.720 --> 40:25.800
You wish!

40:25.880 --> 40:29.480
I could pick up some margarine.
We could roll around in it for a while.

40:55.360 --> 40:57.920
- I've been silly.
- Yeah?

40:58.040 --> 40:59.920
I'm really glad
you're gonna stay.

41:04.480 --> 41:06.520
We might even have
a class together.

41:08.280 --> 41:09.360
- Maybe.
- Look.

41:09.360 --> 41:10.120
- Maybe.
- Look.

41:10.200 --> 41:12.920
There's Kip Pullman.
He's so neat.

41:13.040 --> 41:15.760
Say somethin' to him
when we go by.

41:15.880 --> 41:18.920
- What do you want me to say?
- Anything. I just wanna meet him.

41:20.040 --> 41:21.840
Hey, Kip, buddy.
What's up?

41:21.960 --> 41:24.840
Hey, Henderson, long time no see.
What you been doin'?

41:24.920 --> 41:27.240
Nothin'.

41:27.320 --> 41:31.280
I just wanted to tell you
Bobbie here is madly in love with you...

41:31.360 --> 41:34.200
and trembles at the sight
of your rippling biceps.

41:38.840 --> 41:42.800
- Out of my car, you--
- Wait a second!

41:42.920 --> 41:47.120
I hate you!
Get out of my car!

41:48.040 --> 41:49.800
Temper, temper!

42:40.040 --> 42:43.120
Here it is:
one ten-cent Coke with ice.

42:43.240 --> 42:47.560
And don't take all day
drinkin' it. Please.

42:47.640 --> 42:50.480
Rats! I thought
some of my friends might be here.

42:50.480 --> 42:53.360
Probably a couple of weeks
past their bed time.

42:53.440 --> 42:55.480
There's Dee Dee.
I hope she sees me.

42:55.600 --> 42:57.200
Oh, shit. Dee Dee.

42:59.440 --> 43:01.320
Hiya,John.

43:01.400 --> 43:03.440
- What do you say, Al?
- Not much.

43:03.520 --> 43:06.400
You think if I brought my Mopar
by the shop on Monday...

43:06.480 --> 43:07.760
you could spot-weld
the bumper bracket?

43:07.840 --> 43:11.200
Sure, anything.Just come by
