47:47.560 --> 47:49.400
Girls don't pay. Guys pay.

47:49.480 --> 47:53.320
See, I've only got a 50,
and he doesn't have change.

47:56.560 --> 48:00.120
I can't believe this.
I really cannot believe this.

48:00.960 --> 48:02.640
Here.

48:07.000 --> 48:11.560
- Excuse me. Could you--
- Buy you a bottle of booze?

48:11.600 --> 48:14.640
Yeah, I know. You lost your I.D.
What kind doyou want?

48:14.680 --> 48:18.080
Gee, that's terrific.
Just some Old Harper?

49:00.040 --> 49:02.040
That one over there--
that's Freddy Benson's 'Vette.

49:02.120 --> 49:06.000
He had a head-on collision
with a drunk. Boom!

49:06.040 --> 49:08.080
Didn't have a chance.

49:08.120 --> 49:10.720
He was a good driver too.

49:10.800 --> 49:14.520
It's pretty grim when a guy gets it
and it's not even his own fault.

49:14.600 --> 49:16.440
Needs a paintjob,
that's for sure.

49:16.520 --> 49:18.360
See that over there? That '41 ?

49:18.440 --> 49:21.640
That used to be-- believe it or not--
the fastest car in the valley.

49:21.680 --> 49:24.080
I never got a chance
to race Earl, though.

49:24.120 --> 49:28.840
He got his 1955 in about
the hairiest crash we ever had here.

49:28.880 --> 49:30.720
Jesus, you should've seen it.

49:30.800 --> 49:33.520
Eight kids killed
and both drivers.

49:33.600 --> 49:37.080
Board of Education was real impressed,
so they filmed the whole thing.

49:37.160 --> 49:39.880
Now they show it
in driver's education classes.

49:39.920 --> 49:42.600
Probably see it
if you get lucky.

49:42.640 --> 49:47.200
Course, pretty tough
when they take somebody with them.

49:50.160 --> 49:53.040
You've never had an accident though.
You told me.

49:53.120 --> 49:55.440
Well, I come mighty close.

49:55.480 --> 49:57.960
Almost rolled it
a couple of times.

49:58.280 --> 50:01.880
But I've been just quick enough
to stay out of this graveyard.

50:04.560 --> 50:06.320
Bet you're the fastest.

50:07.800 --> 50:10.600
I've never been beat.
A lot of guys tried.

50:12.080 --> 50:15.120
Seems to me there's more guys lately
than there's ever been.

50:19.920 --> 50:23.120
Sneakin'around
with the Wolfman, baby.

50:26.080 --> 50:30.000
This is gonna strike arawnerve. Mama.
Here's The Platters.

50:30.880 --> 50:32.840
Oh, yes

50:32.880 --> 50:36.040
I'm the great pretender

50:38.080 --> 50:42.360
Pretending
that I'm doing well

50:43.400 --> 50:46.320
My need is such

50:46.360 --> 50:49.520
I pretend too much

50:49.600 --> 50:53.680
I'm lonely
but no one can tell

50:57.040 --> 50:58.800
What are you doin', creep?

51:00.800 --> 51:02.200
Who, me?

51:04.680 --> 51:07.160
No, I'm talkin'
to the other 50 creeps here.

51:11.160 --> 51:13.000
You know Gil Gonzales?

51:15.960 --> 51:17.840
No, I don't.

51:17.880 --> 51:20.440
Don't know Gil.
Well, you oughta.

51:20.520 --> 51:24.040
He's a friend of ours. That's his car
you got your butt parked on.

51:31.600 --> 51:33.560
- Where you goin'?
- Nowhere.

51:33.640 --> 51:36.400
You must be goin' some place.
You left here, didn'tya?

51:37.400 --> 51:39.560
Bring him over here.
I want to show him somethin'.

51:44.200 --> 51:45.720
Bend down here.
Look across here. See?

51:47.560 --> 51:49.480
Right across there.
You see?

51:50.120 --> 51:53.400
- I guess so.
- You scratched it, man.

51:53.480 --> 51:55.920
Where do you get off
sittin' on Gil's car, man?

51:55.960 --> 51:57.880
Sorry.

51:57.960 --> 52:00.080
It's really not much of a scratch.
I don't think you'd see it.

52:00.120 --> 52:05.040
It ain't the size that's in question
here. It's the principle!

52:05.080 --> 52:07.880
Jeez, this is gonna be tough.

52:11.720 --> 52:13.720
What should we do with you?

52:13.800 --> 52:16.280
Tie him to the car
and drag him.

52:23.760 --> 52:25.560
You know Toby Juarez?

52:27.080 --> 52:29.320
He's a Pharaoh, isn't he?

52:32.320 --> 52:33.920
Sure, we know Toby.

52:35.040 --> 52:37.360
We killed him last night.

52:37.440 --> 52:40.280
Tied him to the car
and dragged him.

52:46.160 --> 52:48.200
This is gonna take
some thinkin'.

52:55.160 --> 52:58.160
You better come with us and maybe
take a ride with the Pharaohs, huh?

52:58.240 --> 53:01.000
No, listen, I'd really like to,
but I've gotta--

53:02.800 --> 53:04.680
I'd rather--

53:04.720 --> 53:06.960
I know just howyou feel.

53:07.040 --> 53:09.520
- Shotgun.
- No, I called it.

53:09.560 --> 53:12.040
- When?
- Before we picked you up.

53:12.080 --> 53:14.280
You can't call it for the whole night.
I got it now.

53:14.320 --> 53:16.560
Get in the back, punk.

53:16.600 --> 53:20.160
Will you get in there?
Jesus!

54:03.920 --> 54:06.640
Rock 'n'roll will stand, man!

54:06.680 --> 54:09.120
Whois this
on the Wolfman telephone?

54:09.200 --> 54:11.520
- Hello, it's collect.
- Your name is Collette?

54:11.600 --> 54:14.720
- Yeah, collect call for Wolfman--
- Your name is Collette Call?

54:14.800 --> 54:17.200
- Sir, this is the operator.
- Are you French, operator?

54:17.280 --> 54:20.440
This is a collect call
for Wolfman Jack.

54:20.520 --> 54:23.480
- I love you, operator.
- Is this Wolfman Jack?

54:23.560 --> 54:26.960
- Is Floyd there?
- It's for Wolfman Jack.

54:27.040 --> 54:31.120
I just love listenin' to Wolfman.
My mom won't let me at home.

54:31.160 --> 54:34.040
Because he's a Negro.
I think he's terrific.

54:34.120 --> 54:36.000
Do you know that he broadcasts
from a plane...

54:36.080 --> 54:38.400
that fies around in circles
all the time?

54:38.480 --> 54:39.920
Do you believe that?

54:39.960 --> 54:42.520
Floyd, I love you, Floyd.

54:42.600 --> 54:44.920
Floyd, is this you, Floyd?

54:45.000 --> 54:47.120
Floyd, I cannot look on thee.

54:47.200 --> 54:49.840
Love took my hand
and smiling did reply...

54:49.920 --> 54:52.080
""Who made the eyes but I?""

54:52.120 --> 54:55.320
Floyd, reach out.
Touch my soul, Floyd!

54:55.400 --> 54:57.480
- Your party's ready, sir.
- Hello, Floyd!

54:59.400 --> 55:01.640
You tell her, Wolfman!
He's my man.

55:01.720 --> 55:03.800
When I graduate,
I'm gonna be a Wolfman.

55:03.880 --> 55:07.040
- He broadcasts out of Mexico someplace.
- No, he don't.

55:07.120 --> 55:09.120
I've seen the station
outside of town.

55:10.160 --> 55:13.840
That's just a clearing station.
So he can fool the cops.

55:13.880 --> 55:18.040
He blasts that thing around the world.
It's against the law, man.

55:18.120 --> 55:20.560
- They'll never catch the Wolfman.
- No way.

55:24.040 --> 55:25.960
Man, who cut the cheese?

55:27.640 --> 55:29.560
"" He who smelt it, dealt it.""

55:30.880 --> 55:33.920
There's that bad-ass Chevy again.

55:34.000 --> 55:36.240
Look at that snatch
he's got with him.

55:36.320 --> 55:39.440
- He looks like a wimp.
- Probably is.

55:39.480 --> 55:41.960
Wimps get all the snatch.

55:45.480 --> 55:49.360
Milner ain't gonna beat that.
His time has come.

55:49.440 --> 55:52.960
He's gettin' old.
He ain't as fast as he used to be.

55:55.000 --> 55:57.760
You got two seconds
to get your ass over in your corner.

55:59.000 --> 56:01.040
Don't worry,
I won't rape you.

56:02.400 --> 56:06.320
- You got a bitchin' car.
- Yeah, I know.

56:06.360 --> 56:11.280
In fact, your car's so neat,
we're gonna give you our special prize.

56:11.360 --> 56:13.200
You want me to give it to ya?

56:13.280 --> 56:16.120
Sweetheart, if the prize is you,
I'm a ready Teddy.

56:16.200 --> 56:18.360
Well, get bent, turkey!

56:22.120 --> 56:24.560
Very funny!

56:24.600 --> 56:28.240
What a chop! Ha-ha!
Quit laughing!

56:28.320 --> 56:30.960
-Jump out and fatten their tires.
- Wait a minute.

56:31.000 --> 56:34.680
-Just do what I say!
- All right, boss.

58:12.760 --> 58:14.840
It's a really beautiful
night tonight.

58:16.600 --> 58:19.440
It's a perfect night
for horseback riding.

58:19.480 --> 58:21.600
I was going with a guy
who had horses once.

58:21.800 --> 58:26.480
- Yeah? I had a couple of horses myself.
- Really?

58:26.520 --> 58:29.360
I used them for hunting.
I do a lot of hunting.

58:30.240 --> 58:33.840
Deer mostly.
Got a couple of bear lastyear.

58:33.920 --> 58:37.400
Those were good ponies. Had to
train 'em myself. Took a lot of time.

58:37.480 --> 58:40.400
Do you still have 'em?
We can go for a ride.

58:40.480 --> 58:44.520
No, no. I had to sell 'em
to get these wheels. And a Jeep.

58:45.760 --> 58:47.440
I got a Jeep pickup
with four-wheel drive.

58:47.520 --> 58:49.680
It's got a gun rack.
I use that for hunting mostly.

58:49.760 --> 58:52.880
Why do you kill little animals?
I think that's terrible.

58:52.960 --> 58:54.800
Well, yeah.

58:54.880 --> 58:58.680
I figure with bears, though,
it's me or them.

59:00.800 --> 59:03.600
- I think you're really neat.
- Wait a second.

59:03.680 --> 59:06.720
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean it.

59:06.800 --> 59:10.480
I guess maybe it's the booze
or somethin'.

59:23.200 --> 59:25.280
- Oh! You pinched me.
- I'm sorry.

59:25.360 --> 59:27.600
Let me get my head
over here.

59:27.680 --> 59:29.840
You get up. Okay.

59:29.880 --> 59:32.800
My leg, my leg! Watch it.

59:38.640 --> 59:40.880
I just love
tuck-and-roll upholstery.

59:43.560 --> 59:46.480
Jesus, it's like
Grand Central Station around here.

59:46.520 --> 59:49.440
- Why don't we go someplace else?
- Come on. They won't come back.

59:49.520 --> 59:51.720
Wait a minute.

59:51.760 --> 59:54.720
I got a blanket in the back.
Why don't we go over into the field?

59:54.800 --> 59:56.720
All right. Okay.

59:58.920 --> 01:00:04.040
- How old are you?
- I'm 13. How old are you?

01:00:04.080 --> 01:00:07.720
- I'm only 14.
- I love you, Wolfman.

01:00:10.480 --> 01:00:14.240
We're gonna do the weather
for the valleys and mountain tops.

01:00:14.320 --> 01:00:17.680
It's gonn abe hot.
About 200 degrees in Merced.

01:00:17.720 --> 01:00:19.720
Four hundred degrees
out in Fresno.

01:00:19.760 --> 01:00:23.160
And about 500 degrees
up around the valley somewhere.

01:00:23.240 --> 01:00:26.160
You got
the Wolfman Jack Show!

01:00:40.840 --> 01:00:43.840
This is terrific.
I love miniature golf.

01:00:43.920 --> 01:00:45.920
Is that right?

01:00:46.000 --> 01:00:47.800
I hate it.

01:00:47.920 --> 01:00:50.960
I don't play it too often.
What are we doing here?

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:52.920
We're outta gas, man.

01:00:53.000 --> 01:00:56.320
They don't sell gas here.

01:00:56.400 --> 01:00:59.240
I know.
But we're outta money too.

01:01:19.440 --> 01:01:21.920
What are you punks doin'?

01:01:22.000 --> 01:01:22.960
What's goin' on here?

01:01:25.320 --> 01:01:29.040
Hi, Mr. Gordon.
What's up?

01:01:30.520 --> 01:01:32.960
Henderson?
Curt Henderson?

01:01:33.040 --> 01:01:34.920
Are you with these punks?

01:01:34.960 --> 01:01:37.720
These are just
some friends of mine.

01:01:37.800 --> 01:01:41.280
We're just-- You know.

01:01:41.360 --> 01:01:44.520
You had me nervous there
for a second, huh?

01:01:47.280 --> 01:01:49.560
You didn't leave yet, huh?

01:01:51.720 --> 01:01:54.280
No, I'm not--

01:01:54.440 --> 01:01:57.400
I'm not scheduled to leave
until tomorrow morning.

01:01:57.480 --> 01:01:58.960
Tomorrow?

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:01.520
Hank Anderson's inside.
Come in and say good-bye.

01:02:01.560 --> 01:02:05.800
He brought your name up
at the Moose Hall. You got the check?

01:02:12.840 --> 01:02:15.080
Hank, look who's here.

01:02:17.520 --> 01:02:21.400
How are you, Curt?
What a pleasant surprise.

01:02:21.480 --> 01:02:25.640
Congratulations, my boy.
We're all proud of you. All of us.

01:02:25.680 --> 01:02:30.240
The Moose scholarship went
to the right boy--you.

01:02:30.320 --> 01:02:32.440
And we're all proud of you.

01:02:33.520 --> 01:02:35.400
We're all done out here.

01:02:35.440 --> 01:02:38.080
All done?
What's he mean?

01:02:38.160 --> 01:02:42.320
He means we're all done
having loads of fun out here.

01:02:42.360 --> 01:02:45.720
You can have all the fun you want.
This place is for fun.

01:02:45.800 --> 01:02:48.480
Yes, it is.
Thank you. Thank you both.

01:02:48.560 --> 01:02:49.720
Good luck, son.

01:02:50.960 --> 01:02:54.840
Before I say good-bye, I hope
you'll be taking along with you...

01:02:54.920 --> 01:02:56.960
a little piece of this place.

01:02:57.040 --> 01:02:58.880
I think I have.

01:02:58.960 --> 01:03:00.880
Good. Don't forget us.

01:03:00.920 --> 01:03:03.480
No, I won't forget you,
and you won't forget me.

01:03:03.560 --> 01:03:05.840
- Bye-bye.
- Good-bye and good luck.

01:03:06.960 --> 01:03:11.400
- It was nice to meet ya.
- What he said goes for me too.

01:03:16.240 --> 01:03:19.640
You just might make it
as a Pharaoh yet, boy.

01:03:19.720 --> 01:03:22.680
Someday he'll make
a fine Moose.

01:03:24.680 --> 01:03:26.040
What's the matter?

01:03:28.040 --> 01:03:29.520
The radio's gone.

01:03:31.440 --> 01:03:34.000
That means the car is gone!
Come on.

01:03:48.240 --> 01:03:50.960
Oh, God! Not the car!

01:03:51.000 --> 01:03:55.640
Oh, no! Anything!
Not the car!

01:04:17.360 --> 01:04:19.720
You know,
it doesn't make sense...

01:04:19.760 --> 01:04:22.760
to leave home
to look for home.

01:04:22.800 --> 01:04:26.480
To give up a life
to find a new life.

01:04:26.600 --> 01:04:29.720
To say good-bye to friends you love
just to find new friends.

01:04:29.800 --> 01:04:33.920
- Wait, could you say that again?
- Something Curt said.

01:04:34.000 --> 01:04:36.960
Figures.

01:04:37.040 --> 01:04:39.320
You must've talked his ear off
tryin' to get him to stay.

01:04:39.400 --> 01:04:42.880
No, Steven. That's not true at all.
I didn't say anything.

01:04:42.960 --> 01:04:45.360
Curt just said at dinner tonight...

01:04:45.400 --> 01:04:48.360
that he didn't see
what the big hurry was.

01:04:48.400 --> 01:04:51.360
He thought that he ought to stay
and go to J.C. for a while...

01:04:51.440 --> 01:04:55.800
and try and figure out
what he wanted to do with his life.

01:04:55.880 --> 01:04:58.440
- That sounds logical.
- Do you think so?

01:04:58.480 --> 01:05:01.520
Sure. I think Curt's
probably right, for Curt.

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:04.880
Not for me, though.

01:05:06.760 --> 01:05:08.880
Laurie, look at me.

01:05:13.960 --> 01:05:16.800
You know what I want out of life.

01:05:16.880 --> 01:05:19.280
And it's just not in this town.

01:05:23.480 --> 01:05:26.480
I'm not going with you
to the airport tomorrow.

01:05:35.120 --> 01:05:37.680
- No, Steven, don't.
- Come on.

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:40.400
It's our last night together
for three months.

01:05:40.440 --> 01:05:42.280
I know. But we've been
through this before.

01:05:42.320 --> 01:05:45.280
I'm gonna miss you so much.
I need something to remember you by.

01:05:45.360 --> 01:05:47.640
You don't want me
to forget you, do you?

01:05:48.240 --> 01:05:50.120
No.

01:06:02.160 --> 01:06:04.320
What's wrong?
You're just sitting there.

01:06:04.400 --> 01:06:06.800
- You want to. Go ahead.
- Not like that.

01:06:06.840 --> 01:06:10.160
If you're not gonna remember me
for anything else,just go ahead.

01:06:10.200 --> 01:06:12.480
Come on.
You want it and you know it.

01:06:12.560 --> 01:06:14.440
Don't be so damn
self-righteous with me...

01:06:14.480 --> 01:06:17.400
after all that stuff you told me
about watching your brother.

01:06:17.480 --> 01:06:20.320
You're disgusting!
Get out of my car!

01:06:20.400 --> 01:06:23.520
I told you never
to mention that!

01:06:27.000 --> 01:06:29.960
So, anyhows, the goat killer--

01:06:30.040 --> 01:06:31.880
- Can't we talk about something else?
- No.

01:06:31.960 --> 01:06:35.240
Whenever he strikes, he leaves
a bloody goat's head next to the victim.

01:06:35.320 --> 01:06:37.240
Isn't that creepy?

01:06:37.680 --> 01:06:40.240
They thought he went up to Stockton,
but two nights ago...

01:06:40.320 --> 01:06:44.080
they found the bodies
of Carlie Johnson and Don White...

01:06:44.160 --> 01:06:47.320
right here at this canal
all hacked to pieces.

01:06:47.520 --> 01:06:50.080
Who do you think'll take
the regionals this year?

01:06:50.160 --> 01:06:52.680
Not only were there bloody
goats' heads all around...

01:06:52.760 --> 01:06:55.160
but he had switched parts
of their bodies.

01:06:55.280 --> 01:07:00.680
She had on his arms
and he had on her legs and--

01:07:00.760 --> 01:07:02.440
Wait a second!

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:06.160
Did you hear that?

01:07:06.240 --> 01:07:08.200
- Doyou think it's the goat killer?
- No!

01:07:08.880 --> 01:07:12.560
Listen, I'll go for help
and you stay here.

01:07:12.640 --> 01:07:15.240
No, let's get in this field.

01:07:15.320 --> 01:07:17.680
Come on, come on!

01:07:22.560 --> 01:07:25.600
Maybe if it's the goat killer, he'll get
somebody and we'll see the whole thing.

01:07:25.680 --> 01:07:27.480
I don't want to see
the whole thing!

01:07:28.400 --> 01:07:30.200
I can't see what he's doing.

01:07:30.480 --> 01:07:32.840
Darn it,
I wish I could see.

01:07:32.920 --> 01:07:36.960
I can't see anything.
I don't wanna see anything.

01:07:37.040 --> 01:07:39.320
Just keep him away from me.
That's all I want.

01:07:39.440 --> 01:07:41.280
How do I get into these things?

01:07:41.360 --> 01:07:42.800
We're all right up--

01:07:44.720 --> 01:07:46.320
Debbie?

01:08:02.240 --> 01:08:04.200
- Oh, no! Please! Please!
- Terry.

01:08:04.640 --> 01:08:06.520
- Steve!
- What are you doin' up here?

01:08:06.640 --> 01:08:08.320
Oh, God, Steve.

01:08:08.400 --> 01:08:10.320
Is it safe to come out?

01:08:10.480 --> 01:08:12.520
- Where did you go, anyway?
- Over there.

01:08:12.600 --> 01:08:15.160
- Let's get outta here.
- Where's my 'rod?

01:08:15.280 --> 01:08:17.080
- Your 'rod?
- Yeah.

01:08:17.200 --> 01:08:19.920
Did I introduce you?
This is Debbie. Debbie, this is Steve.

01:08:21.200 --> 01:08:22.800
Well?

01:08:24.319 --> 01:08:26.200
It's in the garage.

01:08:26.319 --> 01:08:28.319
I put it in the garage
for safe keeping.

01:08:28.399 --> 01:08:30.880
I don't want to take any chances
with it.

01:08:30.960 --> 01:08:34.160
It's a good thing too,
because somebody stole our car.

01:08:34.240 --> 01:08:38.279
- That's terrible. What kind was it?
- Where's Laurie anyway?

01:08:38.359 --> 01:08:41.479
- I guess we broke up.
- You broke up? Bull.

01:08:45.840 --> 01:08:48.080
Doesn't look like a gearshift knob.
What is it?

01:08:48.120 --> 01:08:51.479
- Come on, give it back to me.
- What's wrong? You're a tough guy.

01:08:51.600 --> 01:08:55.720
Go ahead and cream me.
Break my arm. See if I care.

01:09:01.840 --> 01:09:03.840
I was just gonna keep it
for a little while.

01:09:03.920 --> 01:09:05.720
You're an ogre, like my father.

01:09:05.840 --> 01:09:10.080
He won't let me stay out late,
or play records, or anything.

01:09:10.160 --> 01:09:12.000
Your fatherwon't let you
stay out late?

01:09:12.080 --> 01:09:13.920
No, he's terrible.

01:09:14.000 --> 01:09:17.479
Once I was out late at a party.
He called the cops.

01:09:17.520 --> 01:09:21.359
Can you imagine?
He had the whole police force there.

01:09:21.520 --> 01:09:25.080
By the way,
where is it that you live, Carol?

01:09:25.200 --> 01:09:27.600
Over on Ramona. Why?

01:09:27.960 --> 01:09:32.359
Oh, no! You thought I'd tell you
where I live?

01:09:32.439 --> 01:09:35.439
Not me. Not old Carol.
The night is young.

01:09:35.520 --> 01:09:38.000
And I'm not hittin' the rack
till I get a little action.

01:09:40.160 --> 01:09:41.439
What do you keep lookin' at?

01:09:41.520 --> 01:09:43.560
Who's that? You know him?

01:09:43.640 --> 01:09:47.080
- He's followin' awful close.
- Grab on to something.

01:09:57.840 --> 01:10:00.040
Hey, man, I'm sorry
if I scared ya.

01:10:00.120 --> 01:10:03.640
You'd have to do a hell of a lot
more than that to scare me.

01:10:03.760 --> 01:10:06.840
I been lookin' all over for ya.
Didn't nobody tell you?

01:10:06.960 --> 01:10:10.520
I can't keep track of all you punks
runnin' around here backwards.

01:10:10.640 --> 01:10:12.760
You're supposed to be
the fastest thing in the valley.

01:10:12.880 --> 01:10:15.640
But that can't be your car.
It must be your mama's car.

01:10:15.760 --> 01:10:18.440
I'm sort of embarrassed
to be this close to you.

01:10:18.520 --> 01:10:21.240
I'm not surprised,
drivin' a field car.

01:10:21.360 --> 01:10:23.200
Field car?
What's a field car?

01:10:23.280 --> 01:10:27.280
A field car runs through the fields,
drops cow shit all over the place.

01:10:27.360 --> 01:10:29.080
That's pretty good.

01:10:29.200 --> 01:10:32.080
I like the color of your car, man.
What's that supposed to be?

01:10:32.160 --> 01:10:35.600
A cross between piss yellow
and puke green, ain't it?

01:10:35.640 --> 01:10:38.000
You call that a paint job,
but it's pretty ugly.

01:10:38.080 --> 01:10:42.040
I'll bet you gotta sneak up on the pumps
just to get a little air in your tires.

01:10:42.160 --> 01:10:45.560
At least I don't have to pull over
to the side just to let a funeral go by.

01:10:45.680 --> 01:10:47.920
Funny. You know what?

01:10:48.000 --> 01:10:50.360
Your car's uglier than I am!

01:10:50.480 --> 01:10:52.400
That didn't come out right.

01:10:56.280 --> 01:10:58.520
Come on, boy.
Let's go. Prove it.

01:10:58.600 --> 01:11:00.800
Why don't you go out and try
to win yourself a few races?

01:11:00.880 --> 01:11:03.480
Then you come on back
and I'll show you a few things.

01:11:03.600 --> 01:11:05.840
Race him. You can beat him.

01:11:05.920 --> 01:11:08.360
That's a tough-lookin' girl
you got with you, man.

01:11:08.440 --> 01:11:11.640
Tryin' to pick up
a few extra bucks baby-sittin'?

01:11:11.760 --> 01:11:15.600
Doll, come and ride with me--
in about ten years!

01:11:15.680 --> 01:11:17.800
Leave her out of this.
This is between you and me.

01:11:35.640 --> 01:11:37.960
He's really fast, isn't he?

01:11:38.040 --> 01:11:39.920
Yeah, but he's stupid.

01:11:42.480 --> 01:11:45.080
Any of you guys know a blonde
in a white T-Bird?

01:11:45.200 --> 01:11:47.000
I know her.
What about it?

01:11:47.120 --> 01:11:49.800
I'm tryin' to find out who she is.

01:11:49.880 --> 01:11:52.480
She's out of your price range, man.

01:11:52.560 --> 01:11:56.040
- My brother's been out with her.
- Price range?

01:11:57.400 --> 01:11:59.160
Are you trying to tell me
she's a prost--

01:11:59.280 --> 01:12:02.960
That's right, she's a $30 Sheri.
Can you imagine that?

01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:06.080
- Thirty bucks for that broad.
- We're thinkin' about different broads.

01:12:06.160 --> 01:12:07.680
Watch it. Fuzz ahead.

01:12:07.760 --> 01:12:10.200
- Where?
- AtJerry's Cherry.

01:12:10.320 --> 01:12:12.480
You can barely see the fender.

01:12:12.560 --> 01:12:14.720
Yeah. We oughta do somethin'.

01:12:14.800 --> 01:12:18.320
I got an idea.

01:12:18.360 --> 01:12:20.240
I got a good idea.

01:12:21.400 --> 01:12:23.320
I think I'm gonna
go over to Burger City.

01:12:23.440 --> 01:12:25.800
Yeah, Laurie's probably over there.

01:12:25.840 --> 01:12:28.600
You think she's got me
worried about where she is, don't you?

01:12:28.720 --> 01:12:30.960
I couldn't care less.

01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:32.880
- Want to come along?
- Yeah, I do.

01:12:32.920 --> 01:12:35.000
- No.
- Make up your minds.

01:12:35.120 --> 01:12:38.280
No, thanks.
We got to report the car missing.

01:12:38.320 --> 01:12:40.720
All right. I'll see ya.

01:12:43.480 --> 01:12:46.000
Shut up! They'll hear us.

01:12:49.360 --> 01:12:52.080
- Listen, Carl--
- Curt.

01:12:53.880 --> 01:12:57.360
Despite you scratchin' Gil's car,
I like you.

01:12:57.440 --> 01:12:59.960
And I know what you'd like
more than anything right now.

01:13:00.600 --> 01:13:03.560
Like every guy in this town, you got
the same secret dream, right?

01:13:04.560 --> 01:13:08.080
You wanna be a Pharaoh.
Go ahead. You can admit it.

01:13:08.160 --> 01:13:10.640
But you didn't think
it was possible, did you?

01:13:12.120 --> 01:13:16.320
Well, tonight...

01:13:16.400 --> 01:13:19.240
I'm gonna give you your chance.

01:13:40.240 --> 01:13:41.840
Get down.

01:13:42.680 --> 01:13:44.800
Okay. Now, you got it?

01:13:44.880 --> 01:13:48.800
- I'm stayin' here. You're on your own.
- Wait a minute, Joe.

01:13:48.880 --> 01:13:52.080
- What if he hears me?
- Listen, listen!

01:13:52.160 --> 01:13:55.600
Look at it this way.
You got three choices.

01:13:55.680 --> 01:13:57.600
One, you chicken out.

01:13:57.680 --> 01:14:00.400
In that case, I let Ants tie you
to the car and drag you around a bit.

01:14:00.440 --> 01:14:02.320
- You don't want that, right?
- No.

01:14:02.360 --> 01:14:06.320
Two, you foul up
and Holstein hears you, and, well--

01:14:06.360 --> 01:14:09.000
- You don't want that, right?
- No, I don't.

01:14:09.040 --> 01:14:13.680
Three, you are successful
and you join the Pharaohs...

01:14:13.720 --> 01:14:17.360
with a car coat and
a blood initiation and all that.

01:14:17.440 --> 01:14:20.280
Wait a minute.
What blood initiation?

01:16:02.560 --> 01:16:04.720
Why don't we go get your Jeep?

01:16:04.800 --> 01:16:07.600
- What are you talking about?
- Your Jeep.

01:16:07.640 --> 01:16:12.080
The one you sold the hunting ponies for.
The one with the four-wheel drive.

01:16:15.600 --> 01:16:17.240
You sure you got
enough slack?

01:16:17.360 --> 01:16:19.320
Yeah, no sweat.
Let's get outta here.

01:16:25.360 --> 01:16:27.920
Come on, Terry.

01:16:29.720 --> 01:16:32.160
Stand by for justice!

01:16:46.880 --> 01:16:49.680
I can't believe it.

01:16:49.720 --> 01:16:52.600
Feeling so good
'cause you're 16.

01:16:57.520 --> 01:17:00.040
Ooh, you come on
like a dream

01:17:00.080 --> 01:17:03.840
Peaches and cream
Lips like strawberry wine

01:17:03.920 --> 01:17:05.640
You're 16

01:17:05.680 --> 01:17:09.200
You're beautiful
and you're mine

01:17:10.520 --> 01:17:12.880
Why are we stopping here?

01:17:13.840 --> 01:17:16.480
- Carol.
- What?

01:17:20.000 --> 01:17:23.520
I don't think that I can
control myself any longer.

01:17:23.600 --> 01:17:27.200
- You can't?
- I've got to have you.

01:17:27.280 --> 01:17:29.200
Me?

01:17:29.280 --> 01:17:31.560
All night you've been sitting there
and you've been so sexy...

01:17:31.600 --> 01:17:34.320
and it's been so hot out here...

01:17:34.400 --> 01:17:37.360
and I can't wait any longer.

01:17:38.320 --> 01:17:40.160
A lot of that
was an act, you know.

01:17:40.240 --> 01:17:43.040
Like my crying.
That was just an act.

01:17:43.120 --> 01:17:45.920
It's been building up inside of me
like a volcano all night.

01:17:46.000 --> 01:17:50.400
If you told me where you lived,
then I could take you home...

01:17:50.480 --> 01:17:53.520
but you won't tell me where you live,
so here we are.

01:17:53.560 --> 01:17:57.040
I mean, I've got to have you.
It's too late.

01:17:57.080 --> 01:17:58.600
It's not too late.
It's never too late!

01:17:58.680 --> 01:18:02.000
231 Ramona. Two-three-one.

01:18:02.080 --> 01:18:04.560
I'll show you.
It's easy to find.

01:18:12.600 --> 01:18:14.600
Hi, Steve.
Mind if I sit down?

01:18:14.640 --> 01:18:17.320
No. Have a seat.

01:18:17.360 --> 01:18:20.480
Just got five minutes off
and I saw you all alone...

01:18:20.560 --> 01:18:22.640
for once.

01:18:22.680 --> 01:18:25.640
- Where's Laurie?
- I don't know.

01:18:25.680 --> 01:18:28.400
I thought you guys'd be together,
this being your last night.

01:18:28.480 --> 01:18:30.800
- We broke up.
- What?

01:18:30.880 --> 01:18:33.520
- It's no big deal.
- What happened?

01:18:33.560 --> 01:18:35.600
Budda, you got an hour left.
Let's get on it.

01:18:35.680 --> 01:18:38.400
All right, all right,
you old fart! Relax!

01:18:39.520 --> 01:18:41.440
Listen.

01:18:41.520 --> 01:18:45.360
I'm off in an hour, and I thought
you'd maybe like to come over.

01:18:49.040 --> 01:18:51.440
- I don't know.
- Well, why not?

01:19:08.400 --> 01:19:10.800
This time it'd just be for fun.

01:19:11.840 --> 01:19:13.680
Okay?

01:19:16.760 --> 01:19:18.960
Okay.
I'll see you later, then.

01:19:20.960 --> 01:19:22.760
Budda, wait.

01:19:23.920 --> 01:19:26.240
Listen, I--

01:19:26.320 --> 01:19:30.360
I gotta get up early in the morning
and I don't think it'd work out.

01:19:50.920 --> 01:19:52.800
I tell you somethin'.

01:19:52.880 --> 01:19:54.880
That thing jumped about
five feet in the air--

01:19:54.960 --> 01:19:56.760
Listen, I still gotta find
that blonde.

01:19:57.520 --> 01:20:00.880
Anyway, we'll catch you tomorrow.

01:20:00.960 --> 01:20:02.560
I guess so. I don't know.

01:20:02.640 --> 01:20:04.520
What do you mean,
you guess so?

01:20:04.560 --> 01:20:07.320
We don't admit a lot of guys
to the Pharaohs.

01:20:07.440 --> 01:20:10.280
We got to steal your car coat,
things like that.

01:20:10.320 --> 01:20:12.200
You gotta
make up your mind.

01:20:12.360 --> 01:20:15.920
Rome wasn't burned
in a night.

01:20:20.200 --> 01:20:22.080
- Let's go!
- I'll see you, boys.

01:20:48.720 --> 01:20:52.120
You only got about five minutes
if you want to talk to the Wolfman.

01:20:52.240 --> 01:20:55.760
Gonna make all your dreams
come true, baby. Hello!

01:20:55.840 --> 01:20:59.600
Would you dedicate a record
to keep me and my girlfriend together?

01:20:59.680 --> 01:21:02.640
-Are you separated?
- We're havin' a little problem.

01:21:02.760 --> 01:21:05.360
I'll bring you right together.
Hold on a minute, man.

01:21:09.000 --> 01:21:11.360
Everything's gonna be
allright now, man, understand?

01:21:11.440 --> 01:21:15.600
I chased the evil spirits away.
Now let me play the record for ya.

01:22:16.320 --> 01:22:18.320
Hey, baby.
What do you say?

01:22:21.440 --> 01:22:24.080
Don't say anything
and we'll get along just fine.

01:22:33.120 --> 01:22:35.640
This is the first time
you've been quiet all night.

01:22:35.760 --> 01:22:38.240
I had fun. Good-bye.

01:22:39.200 --> 01:22:40.680
Bye.

01:22:42.720 --> 01:22:46.320
- Do you like me?
- Yeah, I like you. You're all right.

01:22:46.440 --> 01:22:48.080
But I mean do you like me?

01:22:52.320 --> 01:22:54.080
I like you.

01:22:58.480 --> 01:23:00.440
Okay?

01:23:01.160 --> 01:23:03.200
Couldn't I have something
to remember you by?

01:23:19.040 --> 01:23:21.160
- Bye, kid.
- Gee, thanks!

01:23:21.280 --> 01:23:24.720
It's just like a ring or something.
It's like we were going steady.

01:23:24.840 --> 01:23:27.000
Wait'll I tell Marcia
and everybody!

01:23:27.120 --> 01:23:30.280
- Don't go overboard with this thing.
- I'll see you around.

01:23:43.920 --> 01:23:47.120
I haven't cried so much.
Tears and everything, man.

01:23:47.240 --> 01:23:50.640
I leaned towards the microphone,
I almost shorted myself out!

01:23:50.640 --> 01:23:51.560
I leaned towards the microphone,
I almost shorted myself out!

01:23:51.920 --> 01:23:55.840
- Hold that up.
- You're right about that.

01:23:55.920 --> 01:23:59.600
But why should I leave home
to find a home?

01:23:59.680 --> 01:24:02.680
Why should I leave friends that I love
to find new friends?

01:24:02.800 --> 01:24:04.880
Wait a minute, wait a minute!
I've heard this already.

01:24:05.000 --> 01:24:08.400
Aren't you the one that told me
for eight weeks...

01:24:08.520 --> 01:24:10.640
that you have to leave
the nest sometime?

01:24:10.720 --> 01:24:12.560
I realize that.

01:24:12.640 --> 01:24:15.120
No "realizing".
You've been telling me all summer...

01:24:15.200 --> 01:24:18.480
that it's time to stick your head
out of the sand...

01:24:18.560 --> 01:24:22.080
and take a look at the big,
beautiful world out there somewhere.

01:24:22.160 --> 01:24:25.120
Gimme this thing.
I feel like a midwife.

01:24:25.200 --> 01:24:27.120
I may have been wrong,
Curt.

01:24:27.240 --> 01:24:29.520
Wrong, nothing!
You've been telling me for eight weeks.

01:24:29.640 --> 01:24:31.760
- Goddamn it.
- Yeah, I know.

01:24:31.840 --> 01:24:33.840
You're just mentally
playing with yourself.

01:24:33.920 --> 01:24:36.640
Just relax and we'll talk about it
at the airport.

01:24:37.960 --> 01:24:40.080
Where're you going?

01:24:40.160 --> 01:24:42.560
It's awfully early in the morning.

01:24:42.640 --> 01:24:45.080
- I have a dental appointment.
- Come on, Curt.

01:24:45.200 --> 01:24:48.600
Just relax, will ya?
I'll see you at the airport.

01:24:58.440 --> 01:25:02.040
Some enchanted evening

01:25:02.160 --> 01:25:06.000
You will see a stranger

01:25:06.120 --> 01:25:09.280
You will see a stranger

01:25:09.360 --> 01:25:13.680
Across a crowded room

01:25:13.760 --> 01:25:16.880
And suddenly you'll know

01:25:17.000 --> 01:25:20.280
That she is the one

01:25:28.840 --> 01:25:33.280
- He mustn't have been used to drinking.
- No. He likes to drink. He told me so.

01:25:36.880 --> 01:25:39.520
I knew a man once
who got that sick.

01:25:39.600 --> 01:25:42.640
Billy Weber.
That was ten years ago.

01:25:42.760 --> 01:25:47.600
On his hands and knees like that
he looks like a dog, like old Ginger.

01:25:47.760 --> 01:25:50.800
Sicker'n a dog,
that's for sure.

01:25:55.640 --> 01:25:58.760
- Are you all right?
- Oh, rats.

01:25:59.800 --> 01:26:02.000
I feel terrible.

01:26:06.920 --> 01:26:09.560
The car!
Debbie, look!

01:26:09.640 --> 01:26:12.160
Debbie, that's the car!

01:26:12.240 --> 01:26:14.320
Look. It's sitting right here.

01:26:17.040 --> 01:26:20.360
- Are you sure this is it?
- Yeah, sure. This is it.

01:26:24.080 --> 01:26:26.040
They must've taken
the keys with 'em.

01:26:26.160 --> 01:26:28.800
- Maybe we better go call the police.
- No. Wait a minute.

01:26:28.880 --> 01:26:32.160
I got a better idea.
We'll just steal it back, all right?

01:26:32.240 --> 01:26:34.960
You get some wire-- about a foot.
We can hot-wire it.

01:26:53.040 --> 01:26:55.920
Took the header plugs off?
Expectin' some action?

01:26:56.040 --> 01:26:58.880
Yeah, I think so.
There's some punk lookin' for me.

01:26:58.960 --> 01:27:02.480
Why the hell do they bother?
You've always been number one.

01:27:06.320 --> 01:27:08.920
Been a long time, ain't it?
I'll see you. Thanks.

01:27:26.960 --> 01:27:28.840
Hi, this is my car.

01:27:30.480 --> 01:27:33.280
What I mean is,
somebody stole--

01:27:33.360 --> 01:27:35.480
No, I mean, I lost my car, see?

01:27:35.560 --> 01:27:38.600
And I want to thank
you two guys for retur--

01:27:38.640 --> 01:27:41.800
I mean, now listen.
Now, listen, guys.

01:27:41.840 --> 01:27:46.280
I've been sick, and this kind of
activity can really be hard on a guy.

01:27:46.320 --> 01:27:48.440
Easy. Easy.

01:27:52.080 --> 01:27:53.680
Stop it! Stop it!

01:27:55.760 --> 01:27:58.120
Help! Police! Help!

01:27:58.960 --> 01:28:00.880
Stop it, you creeps!

01:28:18.840 --> 01:28:21.520
- Go, John!
- Get him!

01:28:24.560 --> 01:28:26.480
Come on, get up!
Come on!

01:28:29.520 --> 01:28:32.200
What the hell's
going on here, Toad?

01:28:32.240 --> 01:28:34.120
Man, are you all right?

01:28:34.160 --> 01:28:36.800
Yeah, I'll die soon
and it'll all be over,John.

01:28:36.880 --> 01:28:39.240
Wow, you're just
like the Lone Ranger!

01:28:39.960 --> 01:28:42.520
Listen--
Are you with him?

01:28:42.600 --> 01:28:44.960
You're talking
to the woman I love.

01:28:45.040 --> 01:28:46.840
What happened, man?

01:28:57.240 --> 01:28:59.440
- Hi, Steve.
- Hi,Judy. Hi, Karen.

01:28:59.600 --> 01:29:01.360
Where's Laurie?

01:29:03.600 --> 01:29:05.560
We know where she is.

01:29:05.680 --> 01:29:07.520
So what?

01:29:07.600 --> 01:29:08.880
So nothing.

01:29:08.920 --> 01:29:11.480
It's just that she was
with a really cute guy...

01:29:11.560 --> 01:29:13.600
in a really boss car.

01:29:13.680 --> 01:29:16.400
And we thought you just
might know who it was.

01:29:17.680 --> 01:29:20.520
- I'm sorry, but I wouldn't know.
- We know.

01:29:20.560 --> 01:29:22.480
His name's Bob Falfa.

01:29:32.560 --> 01:29:34.800
Bring two cherry Cokes
with lots of ice.

01:29:34.840 --> 01:29:37.480
No, never mind.
Just bring the ice. Pronto.

01:29:37.520 --> 01:29:39.200
Out! Out!
Get out of the car.

01:29:39.280 --> 01:29:41.320
Steve, what are you doin'?

01:29:41.360 --> 01:29:43.760
Just get out and shut up.
You too. Get out. Get out!

01:29:43.800 --> 01:29:46.760
- What's going on?
- I don't know, but I'm gonna find out.

01:29:54.600 --> 01:29:56.440
I can't believe it.

01:29:56.520 --> 01:29:58.720
You practically get killed
trying to get your car back...

01:29:58.800 --> 01:30:00.600
then you let him have it.

01:30:00.680 --> 01:30:03.000
It's not my car.

01:30:03.120 --> 01:30:05.240
What?

01:30:05.320 --> 01:30:07.120
It is not my car.

01:30:08.400 --> 01:30:10.320
Well, then,
where is your car?

01:30:12.080 --> 01:30:14.000
I don't have a car.

01:30:14.120 --> 01:30:17.120
What about your Jeep?

01:30:17.200 --> 01:30:20.080
How am I gonna get home?

01:30:24.880 --> 01:30:27.920
Where's your car?
I have to hang 'em on a car.

01:30:28.880 --> 01:30:30.640
I need a ride.

01:30:33.840 --> 01:30:37.360
Toad, what happened to you?
Did you lose your car again?

01:30:37.400 --> 01:30:39.600
No, Steve took it.

01:30:41.680 --> 01:30:43.880
I want to go to sleep.

01:30:43.920 --> 01:30:46.560
You got to take it easy
when you drive that car of yours.

01:30:46.640 --> 01:30:49.000
You've got to cruise easy,
baby.

01:30:49.040 --> 01:30:52.640
Don't be doin' any accidents
or anything on me now.

01:30:52.720 --> 01:30:54.800
You know, Terry?

01:30:54.840 --> 01:30:56.800
I had a pretty good time tonight.

01:30:56.880 --> 01:30:59.800
- Come on. You're just--
- No, no. Really, really.

01:30:59.920 --> 01:31:02.000
I really had a good time.

01:31:02.040 --> 01:31:05.280
I mean, you picked me up
and we got some hard stuff...

01:31:05.360 --> 01:31:08.480
saw a hold up
and then we went to the canal.

01:31:08.560 --> 01:31:10.760
You got your car stolen.

01:31:10.800 --> 01:31:13.480
And then I got to watch you
get sick.

01:31:13.520 --> 01:31:16.720
Then you got
in this really bitchin' fight.

01:31:16.760 --> 01:31:20.120
I really had a good time.

01:31:20.240 --> 01:31:23.680
Well, I guess I have a pretty good time
just about every night.

01:31:23.760 --> 01:31:26.120
If I'm not doing
anything tomorrow...

01:31:26.160 --> 01:31:29.080
why don't you give me
a call, okay?

01:31:29.200 --> 01:31:31.000
Yeah, all right.

01:31:31.120 --> 01:31:33.920
I got a little Vespa I play around with.
Maybe, you know--

01:31:34.000 --> 01:31:36.520
Really?
Well, that's almost a motorcycle...

01:31:36.560 --> 01:31:39.360
and I just love motorcycles.

01:31:39.440 --> 01:31:41.760
You do?
Why didn't you say something earlier?

01:31:41.840 --> 01:31:43.640
We wouldn't have had
to go through all the fun.

01:31:45.200 --> 01:31:46.480
I gotta go.

01:31:50.960 --> 01:31:53.080
- Good night.
- See ya.

01:32:54.320 --> 01:32:56.480
Hey, what do you want?

01:32:56.560 --> 01:32:59.280
Push the red switch down.

01:33:03.200 --> 01:33:05.040
I'm looking for this girl.

01:33:05.120 --> 01:33:07.440
Yeah. Aren't we all?

01:33:07.480 --> 01:33:09.360
She's not here.

01:33:09.400 --> 01:33:12.560
Come on in the back.

01:33:12.600 --> 01:33:15.800
You just go around the back.
This way.

01:33:27.440 --> 01:33:30.320
Have a popsicle. The ice box just
broke down and they're melting.

01:33:30.360 --> 01:33:32.280
- You want one?
- No, no, thanks.

01:33:32.400 --> 01:33:35.200
- Listen--
- Have a popsicle.

01:33:35.280 --> 01:33:37.040
Are you the Wolfman?

01:33:38.400 --> 01:33:40.240
No, man.
I'm not the Wolfman.

01:33:43.280 --> 01:33:45.040
Wait a minute.

01:33:53.200 --> 01:33:55.840
Who is this
on the Wolfman's telephone?

01:33:57.200 --> 01:33:59.520
That's the Wolfman.

01:33:59.600 --> 01:34:00.960
He's on tape.

01:34:02.000 --> 01:34:03.360
The man is on tape.

01:34:05.920 --> 01:34:08.280
Where is he now?
I mean, where does he work?

01:34:09.360 --> 01:34:11.440
The Wolfman is everywhere.

01:34:14.320 --> 01:34:16.120
I gotta give him this note.
Shit!

01:34:19.480 --> 01:34:21.520
Here, let me see the note.

01:34:26.480 --> 01:34:29.480
Hell, that's just a dedication, man.
What I can do is relay it.

01:34:29.520 --> 01:34:33.680
- It'll be on tomorrow or Tuesday.
- No, no, this is very important.

01:34:33.760 --> 01:34:36.720
I may be leaving town
tomorrow and it's very important...

01:34:36.800 --> 01:34:40.720
that I reach this girl right now.

01:34:40.800 --> 01:34:43.840
You don't know whether
you're going to leave town or not?

01:34:44.640 --> 01:34:47.440
I'm supposed to go to college
back east tomorrow.

01:34:47.520 --> 01:34:50.960
And I don't know
if I'm going to go. I don't know.

01:34:51.520 --> 01:34:54.800
Wait a minute.
Have a popsicle.

01:34:54.880 --> 01:34:56.920
- No, thanks.
- Sit down a minute.

01:34:57.040 --> 01:35:00.120
- It's early in the morning.
- Damn.

01:35:01.360 --> 01:35:03.200
I can't talk
for the Wolfman...

01:35:03.280 --> 01:35:05.520
but I can tell you one thing.

01:35:07.280 --> 01:35:10.160
If the Wolfman was here,
he'd say, "Get your ass in gear".

01:35:11.840 --> 01:35:13.840
The Wolfman comes in here
occasionally...

01:35:13.920 --> 01:35:17.160
bringing tapes, you know,
to check up on me and what not.

01:35:17.200 --> 01:35:19.760
And the places he talks about
that he's been...

01:35:19.840 --> 01:35:21.680
the things he's seen.

01:35:21.760 --> 01:35:24.840
It's a great big beautiful world
out there.

01:35:24.880 --> 01:35:27.600
And here I sit...

01:35:27.680 --> 01:35:30.760
sucking on popsicles.

01:35:30.840 --> 01:35:32.480
Why don't you leave?

01:35:32.560 --> 01:35:34.320
I'm not a young man anymore.

01:35:36.240 --> 01:35:40.000
The Wolfman gave me my start
in the business, and I like it.

01:35:40.080 --> 01:35:42.440
I tell you what.

01:35:42.480 --> 01:35:44.880
If I can possibly do it tonight...

01:35:45.040 --> 01:35:47.560
I'll try to relay
this dedication in...

01:35:47.600 --> 01:35:49.880
and get it on the air
for you later on.

01:35:50.000 --> 01:35:54.000
That would be terrific.
Really. Thanks.

01:35:54.040 --> 01:35:55.800
Just a minute.

01:35:58.000 --> 01:36:00.720
- It's been a pleasure, really.
- Thanks a lot. Appreciate it.

01:36:00.800 --> 01:36:03.360
Sticky little mothers, ain't they?

01:36:03.440 --> 01:36:05.280
Six or seven of them, right?

01:36:05.360 --> 01:36:08.080
I know. I got a whole
refrigerator full.

01:36:08.120 --> 01:36:10.400
- Thanks a lot. Appreciate it.
- See you later.

01:36:17.880 --> 01:36:20.720
Rock on, baby.
We gonna do it right here.

01:36:20.760 --> 01:36:22.800
Rock 'n' roll
yourself to death.

01:36:22.880 --> 01:36:24.920
Oh, mercy!

01:36:25.040 --> 01:36:27.520
Give me some more!
My, my.

01:36:41.040 --> 01:36:43.120
John, let me go with you.
Come on.

01:36:45.440 --> 01:36:48.080
Nah, man, I can't take you
when I'm racin' somebody.

01:36:48.160 --> 01:36:51.480
Just let me go. I just want to watch.
Or I'll fag you, okay?

01:36:51.600 --> 01:36:53.200
All right. Go ahead.

01:36:57.360 --> 01:36:59.600
Paradise Road.

01:37:04.080 --> 01:37:06.480
Where's this Paradise Road?

01:37:06.560 --> 01:37:09.840
Just follow this street
straight out of town.

01:37:09.880 --> 01:37:14.160
If you're going to race John Milner,
let me out when we get there.

01:37:14.240 --> 01:37:18.320
Why don't you shut up, baby?
You ain't said one word all night long.

01:37:18.400 --> 01:37:20.080
You're a weird broad.

01:37:20.160 --> 01:37:22.960
But you're gonna
appreciate me soon.

01:37:23.000 --> 01:37:26.520
You'll be hanging on for mercy
when I get this sucker rollin'.

01:37:36.720 --> 01:37:38.600
Headin' out to Paradise Road?

01:37:38.640 --> 01:37:40.560
Paradise Road?

01:37:40.600 --> 01:37:43.240
Some guy named Falfa's
goin' up against Milner.

01:37:43.280 --> 01:37:45.520
- He's racing Falfa?
- Yeah.

01:37:45.560 --> 01:37:49.840
Figured something's up. Saw 'em head
out of town real cautious-like and--

01:37:57.200 --> 01:38:00.200
I got a dedication here
for a friend of the old Wolfman.

01:38:00.240 --> 01:38:02.400
He wants me to play
the next song...

01:38:02.480 --> 01:38:05.320
for a blonde young lady
in a Thunderbird.

01:38:05.400 --> 01:38:07.800
A white T-Bird,
you understand.

01:38:07.920 --> 01:38:11.200
My friend's name is Curt
and he wants to talk to you, baby.

01:38:11.280 --> 01:38:13.600
So yo umeet him at Burger City...

01:38:13.680 --> 01:38:16.640
or you can phone
Diamond-3132.

01:38:16.720 --> 01:38:18.560
He's a friend of mine, you hear?

01:38:18.640 --> 01:38:22.640
Little girl, you better call him
or the Wolfman gonna get ya.

01:38:49.600 --> 01:38:52.240
Laurie, what in the hell
are you doing in there?

01:38:52.280 --> 01:38:55.440
- Is she gonna ride with you?
- Mind your own business,John.

01:38:55.480 --> 01:38:59.280
Yeah, she's going with me.
You take care of yourself, man.

01:38:59.320 --> 01:39:01.440
You guys ready?

01:39:48.640 --> 01:39:50.880
You son of a bitch!

01:40:03.160 --> 01:40:05.040
Come on, she's gonna blow.

01:40:05.080 --> 01:40:07.960
I don't know.
Please, don't come near me.

01:40:08.040 --> 01:40:09.840
I'm gonna be sick.
Oh, Steven.

01:40:16.520 --> 01:40:19.600
Oh, Steven!
Please don't leave me.

01:40:19.680 --> 01:40:21.640
- Don't leave me, please.
- I won't.

01:40:21.680 --> 01:40:23.760
I couldn't bear it.
Please.

01:40:23.840 --> 01:40:25.680
I'm not gonna leave you.

01:40:25.760 --> 01:40:27.760
- I'm not gonna leave you.
- Promise me.

01:40:27.840 --> 01:40:29.520
- I promise.
- Do you?

01:40:31.720 --> 01:40:33.400
I'm not gonna leave you.

01:40:45.760 --> 01:40:48.560
That was beautiful, John.
Just beautiful.

01:40:49.920 --> 01:40:53.560
- I was losin', man.
- What?

01:40:55.520 --> 01:40:58.640
He was pulling away from me
just before he crashed.

01:40:58.720 --> 01:41:02.800
You're crazy! You creamed him
from right off the line.

01:41:02.880 --> 01:41:05.680
Shit, Toad! The man had me.
He was beatin' me.

01:41:05.760 --> 01:41:08.080
John, I don't know
what you're talking about.

01:41:08.160 --> 01:41:10.480
It was the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

01:41:10.560 --> 01:41:13.520
He might as well get a wheel chair
and roll himself home.

01:41:13.560 --> 01:41:15.920
Man, you got the bitchinest car
in the valley.

01:41:15.960 --> 01:41:18.760
You'll always be number one.
You're the greatest.

01:41:24.160 --> 01:41:26.400
Look at your glasses, man.

01:41:28.080 --> 01:41:30.640
Okay, Toad.

01:41:30.680 --> 01:41:33.000
We'll take 'em all.

01:41:33.040 --> 01:41:35.760
- All right.
- We'll take 'em.

01:41:35.800 --> 01:41:37.880
Let's get out of here.

01:41:37.960 --> 01:41:39.800
Jesus, what a night!

01:42:17.280 --> 01:42:20.240
- Curt?
- Yes! Yes. This is Curt.

01:42:20.320 --> 01:42:24.080
- Who are you?
- Who were you expecting?

01:42:24.160 --> 01:42:27.120
- Do you drive a white T-Bird?
-A white '56.

01:42:27.160 --> 01:42:29.040
I saw you on Third Street.

01:42:31.320 --> 01:42:32.560
Who are you?
Do you know me?

01:42:32.600 --> 01:42:34.360
Of course!

01:42:34.520 --> 01:42:37.720
- How do you know me?
- It's not important.

01:42:37.800 --> 01:42:40.440
It's important!
It's important to me.

01:42:40.520 --> 01:42:43.600
You're the most beautiful, exciting
thing I've ever seen in my life...

01:42:43.640 --> 01:42:45.800
and I don't know anything
about you.

01:42:45.880 --> 01:42:48.800
Listen, listen--

01:42:48.880 --> 01:42:52.080
- Could we meet some place?
- I cruise Third Street.

01:42:52.120 --> 01:42:54.480
Maybe I'll see you tonight.

01:42:54.520 --> 01:42:56.520
No, I don't think so.

01:42:57.480 --> 01:42:59.640
Tell me your name!
At least tell me your name!

01:42:59.720 --> 01:43:02.040
- Good-bye, Curt.
- Wait a minute!

01:43:04.600 --> 01:43:07.440
Little kiss on your ear.
Goodnight, sweet heart.

01:43:07.480 --> 01:43:09.560
I'll see you later.

01:43:09.640 --> 01:43:12.080
Oh, The Spaniels.

01:43:19.640 --> 01:43:22.560
Good-bye, son.
Call us when you get there.

01:43:26.840 --> 01:43:28.840
I'll miss you.

01:43:32.920 --> 01:43:34.760
Good luck.

01:43:34.840 --> 01:43:37.040
Same to you.

01:43:37.080 --> 01:43:39.680
- Am I gonna see you there next year?
- I'll be there.

01:43:46.240 --> 01:43:48.240
Bye-bye, Curt.

01:43:54.760 --> 01:43:56.480
Stay cool, man.

01:43:58.240 --> 01:44:00.440
And don't do anything
I wouldn't do.

01:44:01.280 --> 01:44:02.880
I'll see you, buddy.

01:44:05.240 --> 01:44:09.320
You probably think you're a big shot
going off like this.

01:44:10.480 --> 01:44:12.560
But you're still a punk.

01:44:12.600 --> 01:44:14.760
Okay, John.

01:44:15.720 --> 01:44:18.320
- So long.
- So long!

01:44:24.080 --> 01:44:25.720
Have a good trip.

